    <etym xml:lang="ru">Восстанавливаем в %i*æx-mæg%i, %i*ærx-næg%i, где %i-næg%i — суффиксальное
        (из %i-na%i + %ika%i), как в <ref type="xr" target="#entry_xærnæg"/>, <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_īwnæg"/>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ægæjnæg"/>, <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_tawnæg"/> и др. Элемент %iæx-%i, %iærx-%i со значением ‘скрепление’,
        ‘скреплять’ и пр. (<mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/><w>*ark-</w></mentioned>) мы
        находим еще в следующих словах: <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æxkænyn"/> ‘запирать’, <ref
            type="xr" target="#entry_æxtong"/> ‘подпруга’ и д. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ærxu"/>
        ‘плотно замкнутый’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ærxæg"/> | %iærxængæ%i ‘сустав’, <ref
            type="xr" target="#entry_arx"/> ‘сук’ и, может быть, <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_arkʼaw"/> ‘клещи’. Для семантического ряда ‘застежка’ — ‘сук’ — ‘клещи’
        ср. <mentioned xml:lang="fa"
            ><lang/><w>giri</w><gloss><q>застежка</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="fa"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>узел</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>сук</q></gloss></mentioned>, и <mentioned xml:lang="fa"
                ><lang/><w>gīra</w><gloss><q>клещи</q></gloss></mentioned>. См. <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_æxkænyn"/>.</etym>
    <etym xml:lang="en">We reconstruct it as %i*æx-mæg%i, %i*ærx-næg%i, where %i-næg%i is a suffix
        (from %i-na%i + %ika%i), like in <ref type="xr" target="#entry_xærnæg"/>, <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_īwnæg"/>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ægæjnæg"/>, <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_tawnæg"/> etc. The element %iæx-%i, %iærx-%i with the meaning
        ‘fastening’, ‘fasten’ etc. (<mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/><w>*ark-</w></mentioned>)
        we can find in other words: <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æxkænyn"/> ‘lock’, <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_æxtong"/> ‘girth’ and Digor <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ærxu"/>
        ‘tightly closed’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ærxæg"/> | %iærxængæ%i ‘joint’, <ref
            type="xr" target="#entry_arx"/> ‘bough’ and, perhaps, <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_arkʼaw"/> ‘pliers’. For the semantic chain ‘clasp’ — ‘bough’ — ‘pliers’
        cf. <mentioned xml:lang="fa"
            ><lang/><w>giri</w><gloss><q>clasp</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="fa"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>knot</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>bough</q></gloss></mentioned>, и <mentioned xml:lang="fa"
                ><lang/><w>gīra</w><gloss><q>pliers</q></gloss></mentioned>. Cf. <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_æxkænyn"/>.</etym>
</entry>
